on, Frankish queen (b. 720)\nBULLET::::- 965 – Meng Chang, emperor of Later Shu (b. 919)\nBULLET::::- 981 – Xue Juzheng, Chinese scholar-official and historian\nBULLET::::- 1067 – John Komnenos, Byzantine general\nBULLET::::- 1441 – Ashikaga Yoshinori, Japanese shōgun (b. 1394)\nBULLET::::- 1441 – Kyōgoku Takakazu, Japanese nobleman\nBULLET::::- 1489 – Bahlul Lodi, sultan of Delhi\nBULLET::::- 1536 – Desiderius Erasmus, Dutch priest and philosopher (b. 1466)\nBULLET::::- 1584 – Steven Borough, English navigator and explorer (b. 1525)\nBULLET::::- 1623 – William Bourchier, 3rd Earl of Bath (b. 1557)\nBULLET::::- 1664 – Stefano della Bella, Italian illustrator and engraver (b. 1610)\nBULLET::::- 1682 – Jean Picard, French priest and astronomer (b. 1620)\nBULLET::::- 1691 – Marquis de St Ruth, French general\nBULLET::::- 1693 – John Ashby, English admiral (b. 1640)\nBULLET::::- 1712 – Richard Cromwell, English academic and politician (b. 1626)\nBULLET::::- 1742 – Evaristo Felice Dall'Abaco, Italian violinist and composer (b. 1675)\nBULLET::::- 1749 – Charles de la Boische, Marquis de Beauharnois, French navy officer and politician, Governor General of New France (b. 1671)\nBULLET::::- 1773 – Johann Joachim Quantz, German flute player and composer (b. 1697)\nBULLET::::- 1804 – Alexander Hamilton, American general, economist, and politician, 1st United States Secretary of the Treasury (b. 1755)\nBULLET::::- 1845 – Henrik Wergeland, Norwegian linguist, poet, and playwright (b. 1808)\nBULLET::::- 1850 – Robert Stevenson, Scottish engineer (b. 1772)\nBULLET::::- 1855 – Pavel Nakhimov, Russian admiral (b. 1802)\nBULLET::::- 1870 – John A. Dahlgren, American admiral (b. 1809)\nBULLET::::- 1892 – Alexander Cartwright, American firefighter, invented baseball (b. 1820)\nBULLET::::- 1910 – Charles Rolls, English engineer and businessman, co-founded Rolls-Royce Limited (b. 1887)\nBULLET::::- 1926 – Gertrude Bell, English archaeologist and spy (b. 1868)\nBULLET::::- 1926 – Charles 